  "elapsed_s": 54.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then, of course, there-- there was a tremendous amount of-- of work that we-- we did [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in organizing [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the expression of the Zionist will and aspiration of the survivors-- organizing the very famous petition that was mentioned and preparing the-- for the first visit of Ben-Gurion.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Not without, by the way, conflicts.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There were on the one hand communist-oriented people who were insistent on people being oriented to go back to their respective countries and build socialism there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And there were the-- the orthodox, the Hasidim, who were demanding the re-establishment of religious Judaism.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And there were some quite bitter conflicts and interesting-- almost adventurous-- events in the-- in the DP camp in Feldafing, as I'm sure that there were in other camps, too.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Eventually then there was the-- the organization of the various DP camps or liberated people in the various occupation of the zones, where a-- an overall organization of the liberated people was organized.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And obviously, as-- as a member of the committee, I was part of that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I, of course, had a tremendous advantage over 99.9% of the people because I had already known that I had at least three sisters surviving, and I had a father in-- in the United States.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I had a fixed point towards which I was gravitating.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And from virtually the first day on, I was looking for ways in which I could speedily get to the United States, which was not very possible or-- or practical.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But I-- I did manage it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And the way I had managed it was itself, I think, terribly meaningful to-- to the story of the post-war [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] problems of the survivors.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
